<details style="margin:18px 0 8px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--border-lt);border-radius:10px;padding:0;overflow:hidden;">
<summary style="cursor:pointer;padding:14px 20px;font-size:13px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:0.3px;color:var(--nhs-dark);background:#F4F8FC;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-lt);list-style:none;">Glossary · click to expand</summary>
<div style="padding:18px 22px;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-sec);line-height:1.7;column-count:2;column-gap:30px;">
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>DCB0129</strong> · clinical safety standard for the <em>manufacturer</em>. The supplier's responsibility.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>DCB0160</strong> · clinical safety standard for the <em>deploying</em> organisation (e.g. a commissioner running HomeTest locally). Requires a local Clinical Safety Officer route, local hazard log, local deployment sign-off.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>CSO</strong> · Clinical Safety Officer. The named clinician who signs off DCB0129 (supplier-side) or DCB0160 (deployer-side) for a given configuration.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>CATR</strong> · Clinical Assurance to Release. The clinical safety sign-off before a deployment is allowed to handle live patient data. Sits with Aisha (Clinical / CSG).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>DPIA</strong> · Data Protection Impact Assessment. The risk assessment for any processing of personal data. Required before go-live.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>DSA</strong> · Data Sharing Agreement. The contract between data controllers (e.g. NHSE, the commissioner, the supplier) governing what data flows where.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>DPA</strong> · Data Processing Agreement. The contract with a data processor (typically the supplier acting on behalf of a controller).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>Controller / Processor</strong> · GDPR roles. Controller decides why and how data is processed; processor does the processing on the controller's behalf. NHSE is controller for the foundation. The commissioner is controller for the testing purpose. The supplier is typically processor.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>Lawful basis</strong> · the legal ground under GDPR for processing personal data. Examples: patient consent, public task, direct legal direction.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>ROPA</strong> · Record of Processing Activities. The supplier's register of what personal data they process, why, and how.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>IAO</strong> · Information Asset Owner. The named NHSE-permanent-employee who owns the information asset and is the final IG sign-off. NHSE policy requires this role to be a permanent employee, not a contractor.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>DPO</strong> · Data Protection Officer. The statutory IG lead (Ngozi's role).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>FHIR</strong> · Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources. The international standard for exchanging healthcare data. The platform uses FHIR APIs for clinical data flows.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>UKAS / ISO 15189</strong> · UK Accreditation Service / international standard for medical lab quality. Standard NHS lab accreditation. The lab must hold UKAS accreditation against ISO 15189.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>ISO 27001</strong> · international standard for information security management. Suppliers handling NHS data are expected to hold ISO 27001 certification.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>EOI</strong> · Expression of Interest. A supplier's formal application to join a procurement framework. Plan A only (PA23 framework); under SBS PSR bridge or commissioner-led the entry mechanic differs.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>Atamis</strong> · the NHS procurement portal where suppliers submit formal applications.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>PA23 / PSR / DPC Framework</strong> · the three candidate procurement regimes. PA23 = Procurement Act 2023 (Plan A). PSR = Provider Selection Regime (used in the SBS bridge interim and Plan C). DPC = Digital Primary Care Framework (Plan B).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>MOU</strong> · Memorandum of Understanding. The contracting vehicle used for Alpha and Beta only. Retires when the formal framework instrument is awarded.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>ACE</strong> · the call-off vehicle used for the <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="hiv">HIV</span> Alpha deployments through the <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="hiv">SBS Sexual Health Framework</span> Lot 1.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>MVP</strong> · Minimum Viable Product. The first-iteration position; centralised invoicing and other refinements are deferred to later iterations.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>MI</strong> · Management Information. Dashboards and reports on activity, volumes, performance.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>KPI / SLA / TAT</strong> · Key Performance Indicator / Service Level Agreement / Turnaround Time. Standard performance metrics.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>LA / ICB</strong> · Local Authority / Integrated Care Board. Two of the candidate commissioner types.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong><span class="cfg-mark" data-config="psa-as">MDT</span></strong> · Multi-Disciplinary Team. Standard clinical escalation route in acute care.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>CAG / CSG</strong> · Clinical Advisory Group / Clinical Safety Group. The clinical governance bodies that hold safety oversight.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>ICO</strong> · Information Commissioner's Office. The UK data protection regulator. Statutory reporting threshold for breaches.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>Caldicott</strong> · Caldicott principles, a long-standing NHS framework for handling patient-identifiable data responsibly.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>Three-tier pricing</strong> · the working commercial structure: <em>mobilisation fee</em> (one-off for a new commissioner setup), plus <em>activity payment</em> on cost per valid result, plus a <em>volume floor</em> (a guaranteed minimum volume below which the supplier is still paid).</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>Shadow / dual-run / live</strong> (tariff states) · standard NHS tariff introduction stages. <em>Shadow</em> = tariff calculated but not paid; used to model behaviour. <em>Dual-run</em> = a percentage paid through the new tariff, the rest through the old route. <em>Live</em> = full payment through the new tariff.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>PbR / HRG / CDS / SUS</strong> · the NHS payment plumbing for acute activity. Payment by Results / Healthcare Resource Groups / Commissioning Data Set / Secondary Uses Service. Activity is recorded in CDS, classified into HRGs, and paid via PbR using SUS as the data source.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>NHSBSA / OPCS</strong> · NHS Business Services Authority (pharmacy payments, drug tariff). OPCS = the classification of clinical procedures used in coding.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>P1 / P2 / P3</strong> · clinical safety incident severity bands. P1 highest (immediate patient harm), P3 lowest.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>FDP / SPR</strong> · Federated Data Platform / Single Patient Record. National NHS data infrastructure HomeTest aligns to rather than replicating.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>PTT</strong> · the Programme &amp; Transformation Team / clinical-area governance team responsible for legal directions in a given clinical area.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;break-inside:avoid;"><strong>NHS App / NHS Login / NHS Notify</strong> · the three NHSE platform foundation services. App = patient-facing surface. Login = identity. Notify = messaging.</p>
</div>
</details>
