  <div style="font-size:13.5px;color:#212B32;line-height:1.7;">The commissioner walks in once and leaves with a signed call-off. Where the bilateral route used to take six to nine months, the published catalogue and inherited framework templates compress the buy into weeks. The platform broker holds the supplier and clinical assurance complexity in the back office; the commissioner sees one front door. The lane exposes the role on which the model most depends: the framework administrator, who has to be the steward of the catalogue itself.</div>
