<div class="decision-box">
<h4>Open decisions</h4>
<p><strong>Result delivery failure handling.</strong> What the platform does if a result is missing, late, or fails delivery via NHS App. Backstop process not yet specified.</p>
<p><strong>Reactive result clinical pathway.</strong> What happens clinically when a result is reactive or abnormal. Architecture is in place: Reactive Results API implemented, supplier obligation of clinical follow-up before escalation, platform-side safety control withholds the result from user-visible release and triggers the clinical pathway, data controller split defined across platform, commissioned service and supplier. Onward referral routes mapped per configuration (LA <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="hiv">sexual health</span> for <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="hiv">HIV</span>, <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="psa-as">acute trust</span> for <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="psa-as">PSA-AS</span>, GP for <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="ida">iron deficiency anaemia</span>, CVKM pathway for cardiovascular). Hardening pre-BAU: watertight safety-net evidence is a Beta exit criterion; hard-coded fail safes still under validation.</p>
<p><strong>Repeat-test cadence.</strong> How often patients should retest after a non-reactive or in-range result. Signposting and cadence rules vary by configuration and are not yet codified.</p>
<p><strong>Patient withdrawal.</strong> What happens if a patient orders, then withdraws, or doesn't return the sample. Sample-rejection and no-return handling are operational details still to define.</p>
</div>
