<div class="lane-synthesis" style="margin:24px 0 0;padding:18px 22px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#F4F8FC,#E8F1F6);border-left:4px solid #005EB8;border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;">
  <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.4px;color:#005EB8;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Lane synthesis &middot; what is happening across the actors</div>
  <div style="font-size:13.5px;color:#212B32;line-height:1.7;">Most of the work in the live service sits with the supplier: kit out, sample back, result delivered. The commissioner watches the MI; the platform brokers the data flow and the reactive support paths. The centre does not run the service. Its job is to make the pathway predictable, the data clean, the exceptions handled, and to surface the reactive cases (unsafe-address delivery, undelivered results, withdrawal) into a clinical-safety net that does not fall to the supplier alone.</div>
</div>
<!-- ==================== LANE 4: COMMERCIAL SETTLEMENT ==================== -->
<div class="swimlane-section" id="lane-3">
<div class="sl-card">
<div class="sl-head">
<h3>4. Commercial settlement</h3>
<p>How money flows between <strong>Sarah (commissioner)</strong>, <strong>Joe (supplier)</strong>, and <strong>David (NHS Commercial)</strong> who holds the rules. Near-term shape: direct commissioner-to-supplier invoicing &mdash; the supplier invoices the commissioner for services consumed at the rates and frequency in their call-off; NHSE sits outside the payment flow. Future-state option (deferred until volumes mature): a small platform fee per transaction to make the system self-sustaining, mirroring how existing NHS purchasing bodies work. Either way the centre is accountable for market shaping and supplier onboarding; not for local contract ownership or local billing. Today's Recommendation Paper sits on the near-term shape; a platform fee remains a future option for a later iteration once call-off volumes through the platform make it viable. <span class="gap-flag">Initial payment route during early operation may differ from the steady-state model</span>.
 </p></div>
