<div class="sl-cell foundation"><span class="so-tag foundation-tag">Foundation</span><strong>I publish the framework pricing.</strong>Working structure: <strong>three-tier pricing</strong>. Tier 1 <em>mobilisation fee</em> (one-off payment to the supplier covering setup costs when a new commissioner onboards). Tier 2 <em>activity payment</em> based on cost per valid result (the supplier gets paid for each test that the patient returns, the lab analyses, and a result is delivered — not for each kit dispatched). Tier 3 <em>volume floor</em> (a guaranteed minimum volume below which the supplier is still paid, so the commercial model holds even at low uptake). Same terms for every commissioner. Pricing schedule sits inside the framework instrument. <span class="gap-flag">Flat per-kit pricing was rejected through RFI and supplier forums; subscription rejected at strategic level. Final position on the activity unit is carried as A9 in the recommendation paper. <span class="cfg-mark" data-config="psa-as">PSA Active Surveillance</span> is a separate model (per-patient-per-year Monitoring Episode), not a variant of this question.</span></div>
